        "id": "1637145392470286528",
        "text": "If inertia’s about “how tools feel,” what’d count as a fundamental change — is it about swapping out the input method, redesigning config formats, or something else entirely? I’m asking because we tend to blame surfaces, but sometimes friction’s buried three layers down.",
